-- Dick's Sporting first-quarter profit rises
-- 
-- Wed May 23, 2007 7:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/23/us-dickssporting-results-idUSWNAS221720070523

 

 (Reuters) - Sporting goods retailer Dick's Sporting Goods Inc. ( DKS.N ) posted a higher quarterly profit as comparable store sales rose. 

 The Pittsburgh-based company said first-quarter net income was $21.7 million, or 38 cents a share, compared with $11.4 million, or 21 cents a share, a year ago. Net sales rose 28 percent to $823.6 million. For the latest first quarter, analysts on average expected the company to earn 37 cents a share, on revenue of $851.8 million, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by Amitha Rajan in Bangalore)